{"questionId":"21642","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Charlotte decides to model the shape of a cupcake to calculate its volume.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/4245581b17486dca580f995d41ea866bd7ac7821.png\"></p>\n<p>From rotating a photograph of her cupcake she estimates that its cross-section passes&nbsp;through the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, where all units are in&nbsp;centimetres. The cross-section is symmetrical in the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis, as shown below:</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/76ffc5e524ee327e6a1ca2525800669c038d0e0b.png\"></p>\n<p>She models the section from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo></math> as a straight line.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Charlotte models the section of the cupcake that passes through the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math> with a quadratic curve.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the equation of the least squares regression quadratic curve for these&nbsp;four points.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>975</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>56</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>974630</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>55919</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6569</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><strong><br></strong><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21642","referenceCode":"21M.2.AHL.TZ1.4b.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the equation of the least squares regression quadratic curve for these four points.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.13—Non-linear regression","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}